Instructions for running existing JAR file:

1. Download "pizzalist.jar" JAR file from target/ directory in github repository.
2. Execute JAR file using following command,
	$java -jar pizzalist.jar <sourcefilepath> <targetfilepath>
Example: "$java -jar pizzalist.jar sample.txt output.txt"

Instructions to build new JAR file with existing project:

1. Import source code and pom.xml from repository to Maven Environment.
2. Run command "mvn clean install" - This command deletes existing target/ directory, compiles the source code, runs unit test cases and builds new target/ directory with a JAR file named "pizzalist.jar"
3. Now execute the JAR file as instructed. 
